        q: "Your landing page has a 2% conversion rate and traffic is strong and qualified. The creative director wants a full redesign. Before agreeing, how do you diagnose the copy problem?",
        a: "Problem: A full redesign is expensive and time-consuming, and it risks throwing away elements that are working alongside the ones that are not. Before redesigning, you need to know whether the issue is copy, design, offer, or audience mismatch.\n\nApproach: Start with session recordings in Hotjar or FullStory to watch where users scroll to and where they drop off - if 70% of visitors never reach the CTA, the top-of-page copy is not holding attention. Then run a 5-second test: show the landing page for 5 seconds and ask what the product does. If participants cannot articulate the value proposition, headline clarity is the primary fix. Check the ad-to-page message match: if the ad says 'increase your ROAS' and the headline says 'grow your business,' there is a message mismatch that deflates conversion before any other variable matters.\n\nResult: most 2% conversion problems trace to a weak headline, a missing trust signal above the fold, and a CTA that describes an action rather than an outcome. Identify the highest-impact fix and run one A/B test at a time before committing to a full redesign.",
